{"lemma":"عاقِدِي","slug":"عاقِدِي","root":"ع.ق.د","root_slug":"ع-ق-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29886"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%90%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%8A"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"who ties, who knots"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"who contacts a girl to an affianced spouse"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"legally competent to enter a contract"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of عَقَدَ (ʕaqada, “to knot, to tie”)."},"ipa":["/ʕaː.qid/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29886","headword_ar":"عَاقِدٌ","root":"Eqd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has confessed herself to have conceived;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has closed her vulva upon the sperma of the stallion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for she then twists her tail as if tying it in a knot, and it is thereby known that she has conceived:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, L:) and a she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twisting her tail as if tying it in a knot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has so twisted her tail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the occasion of her conceiving;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that it may be known that she has conceived:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaAqidu","text_ar":"عَوَاقِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b2-  And A she-gazelle"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the end of her tail twisted"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as if tied in a knot"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bending her neck in lying down:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raising her head in fear for herself and her young one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And A gazelle"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"putting his neck upon his rump,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having bent it to sleep:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having put his neck upon his rump:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl. as above. (O, L.) ―         -b3-  And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a EaAqidFA Eunuqahu","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ عَاقِدًا عُنُقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came twisting his neck by reason of pride."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, O, L.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqidN","text_ar":"عَاقِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied as an epithet to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqiT","text_ar":"اَقِط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] meaning That"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the water has gone, and which is thoroughly cooked."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHát, TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kavo'N","text_ar":"كَثْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  Also The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"space called the"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hariym","text_ar":"حَرِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a well;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is around it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Hawolahu","text_ar":"مَا حَوْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, M, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is around the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hrym","text_ar":"حريم"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the K [and O],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA HuwolahaA","text_ar":"ما حُوْلَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is around the well;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the former is the right. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","L","TA","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}